My father died at midnight

By Xia Chunping, deputy editor-in-chief, China News Service

PUBLISHED: March 16,2020

This is a tough Genzi years, the individual life in this year is particularly vulnerable.

"closed city" in Wuhan, the winter is so long, and the spring came extremely difficult. March 4 is Wuhan "closed city" on the 42nd Day, 11:25 at night, have been lying in bed ready to go to bed, I found the mobile phone vibration, the caller ID is "mother. I felt a "click" and a sense of foreboding crept over me. In recent years, my mother and my sister live in Wuhan, sleep regularly, every night at 9:00 on the dot, never call me late at night. Over the phone came my mother's frantic voice: "Haruhira, Oh no, the hospital called, your father... " I rolled over and got out of bed, rushing downstairs from the Golden Shield Hotel in Guanggu, Wuchang, where I work as a reporter for the "epidemic" news team of the China News Service, to the Changhang hospital in Hankou.

Car from the south to the north through the Yangtze River Bridge, "closed city" in Wuhan, the night quiet people can hear their own breathing, under the reflection of the cold moon of the Yangtze River, quietly flowing, such as crying. Dad's voice, his smile, all the way through my head...

Parents 45 years ago

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The Spring Festival in the year of Gengzi makes her mother especially worried. She has ordered numerous incense sticks at home and prayed that her father, who has been in hospital for many years, can survive the winter-spring festival which is covered by the plague. Mother is most worried about in Wuhan "closed city" This special period dad if something happens, it will be worse...

While working in Wuhan these days, I found time to go to the hospital to see my father several times. Every time I went, my father, who had an oxygen tube in his mouth, was asleep with his eyes closed, unaware that the city was closed. I could only ask Liu, the nurse, about my father's Day. I remember the last time I went to the hospital to see my father on Sunday evening three days ago. My father went to bed wearing his usual oxygen inhaler, but he wore an extra mask than before. This is the standard for Wuhan residents suffering from new coronavirus pneumonia, the infirm elderly patient did not dare to take it off even when he was sleeping. The 90-year-old father, who has been suffering from Alzheimer's and chronic obstructive pulmonary disease for years, has spent six years in a hospital bed, his organs failing until he needed oxygen tubes and nasal feeding to keep him alive.

At 12:15 am on March 5, my brother-in-law and I, who live in Hankou, arrived at the hospital. My sister told me that my mother had insisted on coming, after my sister, brother-in-law's resistance, grief in the Mother did not come easily infected hospital.

The car in the hospital just stopped at the entrance to the hospital department building, I hurriedly got off the car, from the stairway to climb up the Hospital Department 7 Floor of Dad's ward. The doctor told me that 40 minutes ago, Dad stopped breathing... ... Two white-suited morgues were carrying my father in a yellow body bag wrapped in a sheet and carrying him out of the ward on a stretcher. As a relative of the deceased, I accompanied the body on a Gurney and took a special elevator down to the hospital morgue.

The mortuary, about 200 meters from the inpatient building, was hidden in a very inconspicuous place in the southwest corner of the hospital. On the way to the mortuary, the "Gurgling" sound of the bodies being crushed on the road by the stretcher broke through the quiet midnight of the hospital.

The hospital told me that the Wuhan New Crown Pneumonia Epidemic Prevention and control headquarters stipulated that the bodies of the deceased who died of illness during the "closure of the city" shall be cremated as early as possible by the Hankou funeral home, and their families shall not follow the hearse to the funeral home where they were cremated, the ashes of the dead will be collected after the end of the epidemic in Wuhan. Under the "closed city" state of Wuhan makes all this become so blunt and inhuman: Father should have the dignity, decent farewell ceremony can not be carried out, relatives of the deceased filial desire was crushed.

The doctor on duty at the hospital mortuary suggested that Dad's body should be changed into a shroud before being put into an ice coffin that night. Unprepared, I had to buy a set of the most expensive Tang suit seven-piece set of shroud from the on-duty Master as Dad's final "dress. ".

The two men expertly dressed their emaciated father in a padded jacket, dark purple cotton trousers and a dark purple robe, wearing a purple cap, seven layers of black shoes and a face cloth to hide his face, and then you put the Red Lid on.

Lying in an ice coffin, my father was as calm and serene as he had been in his prime, exhausted after a hard day's work. I held dad's hand tightly, and the warmth of his hand gave the impression that he was still alive. I could clearly see the black and purple scars on the back of my father's hand from years of injections. Dad's hand soft, soft, as when I was a child holding hands, still warm and reluctant to give up. I can't remember a time other than my childhood when I held my father's hand for such a long time.

When I was admitted to the Wuhan University from the countryside several decades ago, my father took off the mechanical watch he had worn for many years and gave it to me. It was the first time in my life that I put on a watch, and I have since been able to remember the precise time of my life.

I gently lifted the yellow face cloth and lifted the white face cloth carefully, holding my breath and trembling. My father's old, serene, familiar face caught my eye, and his mouth was free of that suffocating, repulsive mask. I stroked my father's still warm forehead, his eyes that would never open again, his nostrils that would never breathe again, his ears that could never hear his children, his lips that could never make another sound of pain... Under the incandescent light of the narrow, gloomy mortuary, my father's features looked handsome, handsome, elegant, and full of life.

It's a little after 1:00 in the morning, the mortuary attendants and two men on duty reminded me, and I realized that they were waiting for my final goodbye before I could proceed to the next stage -- Lock the lid on the ice coffin, plug it in and freeze it.

I bent down and bowed my head, gently kiss my father's cheek cheek cheek cheek cheek, it is so warm, such as a baby delicate, smooth. I reluctantly raised his head straight, with a white face cloth covered his father's head again, and then picked up the yellow face cloth gently spread on the white face cloth. Trance, I feel that the two pieces of thin light satin cover seems to be very heavy, afraid it pressed Dad "suffocation. ".

The night was cold and still. It was 2:00 a.m. the next day when I left the hospital morgue and returned to the local hotel. Is the night, no tears, no language, no sleep, only one after another out of the thick smoke.

In the early morning hours of March 5,2020, Wuhan was under siege
